# Architecture

**Hierarchy:** PROJECT_DEFINITION (§10, §16) → ARCHITECTURE → current epic. Document deviations explicitly.

## Structure

```
cabine-ia/
  api/       NestJS — FSM, jobs, themes, SQLite, R2, secrets
  kiosk/     React + Vite — guest/operator UI, camera, QR
  scripts/   Start api + kiosk (orchestration only)
  docs/      Specs and runbooks
```

## Principles

- **State:** NestJS is sole owner of booth/session state. Kiosk renders API snapshots and sends commands.
- **Phases:** Guest screen = API `phase` field. No parallel client state machine.
- **Module borders:** Keep boundaries explicit within each app (NestJS modules in api/, feature folders in kiosk/). No cross-imports between api/ and kiosk/ — ever.
- **Boundary:** api ↔ kiosk communicate via HTTP on localhost only. No shared packages, shared types/, or code imports across apps.
- **Secrets:** API keys, cloud creds, scene prompts — api/ only, never in kiosk bundle.
- **Themes:** Versioned packs in api/themes/. Kiosk receives metadata via API only.
- **Delivery:** Guest QR → presigned HTTPS (R2). Raw captures ephemeral in api/data/tmp/.
- **Stack:** TypeScript in both apps (separate package.json). NestJS + React + Vite + SQLite.

## Responsibilities

| App | Owns |
|-----|------|
| api/ | Session FSM, generation, delivery, persistence, operator downloads |
| kiosk/ | Fullscreen UI, camera, face detection, QR display, API client |

Full details: docs/ARCHITECTURE.md
